      <description>&lt;!-- [DocumentBodyStart:37aa6720-6912-465d-ba50-b21603ac74ff] --&gt;&lt;div class="jive-rendered-content"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Another great option is to store the Zenoss RRD files in a RAM disk or swapfs filesystem.&amp;#160; You'll need to modify the scripts to rsync the RRD files to stable storage every hour or so and at startup and shutdown, but it pretty much eliminates performance issues due to disk IO.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- [DocumentBodyEnd:37aa6720-6912-465d-ba50-b21603ac74ff] --&gt;</description>
